{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_32","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `io.ktor:ktor-sse-jvm:3.2.2`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-6955-fails-java-run-io.ktor-ktor-sse-jvm-3.2.2-9defa3fd\n\nThe original Java runtime failure appears to have been understood and addressed: the first failing run shows 4 assertion failures because `ServerSentEvent.toString()` in 3.2.2 emits `event:` before `data:` (`human-intervention-logs/io.ktor:ktor-sse-jvm:3.2.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-18T13-46-07-970413Z.log`). After that, later runs passed, including native verification: `human-intervention-logs/io.ktor:ktor-sse-jvm:3.2.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-18T13-47-01-953108Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/io.ktor:ktor-sse-jvm:3.2.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-18T13-48-40-234559Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/io.ktor:ktor-sse-jvm:3.2.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-18T13-49-03-772016Z.log`, and `human-intervention-logs/io.ktor:ktor-sse-jvm:3.2.2/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-18T13-47-40-229246Z.log` all show 7/7 tests successful.\n\nThe most likely failing stage is metadata generation / agent setup, not the library test itself. `human-intervention-logs/io.ktor:ktor-sse-jvm:3.2.2/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-05-18T13-47-38-482220Z.log` fails with `Could not find agent library native-image-agent on the library path` and `libnative-image-agent.so: cannot open shared object file`, which points to a GraalVM environment/toolchain problem while running `generateMetadata`. Metrics also ended in failure after 1 iteration with no dynamic-access coverage recorded.\n\nRecommended manual next steps:\n1. Review the preserved branch and keep the test expectation updates for the 3.2.2 wire-format ordering change, plus the metadata `index.json` URL/description additions.\n2. Fix the GraalVM/native-image agent setup so `native-image-agent` is available on the library path, then rerun `./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=io.ktor:ktor-sse-jvm:3.2.2`.\n3. After metadata generation succeeds, rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.ktor:ktor-sse-jvm:3.2.2` and regenerate coverage if available."}}
